<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="507" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94116/96: Telegram (part air)</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-07T21:00:00+01:00">September 7, 1938—9
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 9—8:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>181. My 167, August 9, 7 p.m. Chinese permanent delegate has addressed a
                            further communication to Secretary General containing additional
                            information concerning alleged use of poison gas by Japanese troops in
                            China. Communication states that after the first use of gas at Matang
                            gas has continued to be used on many occasions up to and including
                            present drive on Hankow. Note asks that communication be circulated to
                            members of Council, Assembly and Advisory Committee.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucknell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
